
[1]passionate

   PAS'SIONATE, a.

   1. Easily moved to anger; easily excited or agitated by injury or
   insult; applied to persons.

   Homer's Achilles is haughty and passionate.

   2. Highly excited; vehement; warm; applied to things; as passionate
   affection; passionate desire; passionate concern.

   3. Expressing strong emotion; animated; as passionate eloquence.

   PAS'SIONATE, v.t. To affect with passion; to express passionately. [Not
                                   used.]
